# Tokyo Station

This is an image of **Tokyo Station** (東京駅), located in **Tokyo, Japan**.

The distinctive red-brick building with its characteristic Baroque Revival architecture is one of Japan's most iconic railway stations. Built in 1914, it features the recognizable dome and ornate façade visible in this photo. The modern skyscrapers surrounding the historic station in the background reflect Tokyo's blend of traditional and contemporary architecture. The wide plaza in the foreground is Marunouchi Square, which was renovated and reopened in 2012.
